## 1. Abstract
This report presents the design and implementation of an Attendance Management System developed as an HCI project. The system is user-friendly, accessible, and visually appealing, following HCI principles to ensure a positive experience for all users. Screenshots and step-by-step guides are included for clarity.

---

## 2. Introduction
The Attendance Management System is designed for educational institutions to simplify attendance tracking. The project focuses on usability, accessibility, and attractive design, making it easy for Admins, Teachers, and Students to interact with the system.

---

## 3. Project Objectives
- Simplify attendance management
- Ensure accessibility for all users
- Provide clear, attractive dashboards
- Use simple language and intuitive navigation
- Meet HCI and usability standards

---

## 4. System Overview
- **Technology:** ASP.NET Core, SQL Server, HTML, CSS, JavaScript
- **Users:** Admin, Teacher, Student
- **Main Features:**
  - Role-based dashboards
  - Attendance marking and statistics
  - User, course, and session management
  - Secure login and password reset

